You are an expert enterprise business analyst and quality auditor.
Your task is to identify any contradictions, conflicts, or inconsistent terminology across the following set of user stories.

User Stories:
{% for story in stories %}
---
ID: {{ story.id }}
Title: {{ story.title }}
Story: {{ story.user_story_text }}
Acceptance Criteria:
{% for ac in story.acceptance_criteria %}
- {{ ac }}
{% endfor %}
{% endfor %}

Analyze the stories as a complete set. Look for:
1. Contradictions: One story states something that directly conflicts with another (e.g., different authentication methods, conflicting business logic).
2. Inconsistent Terminology: The same business concept is referred to by different names, or different concepts use the same name.
3. Logical Conflicts: Sequencing or flow conflicts.

Output your assessment in the following raw JSON format:
{
  "consistent": true/false,
  "conflicts": [
    {
      "story_ids": ["string", "string"],
      "conflict_type": "CONTRADICTION" or "TERMINOLOGY" or "LOGICAL",
      "description": "Detailed explanation of the contradiction or inconsistency",
      "severity": "CRITICAL" or "MAJOR" or "MINOR"
    }
  ],
  "feedback": "Overall summary of consistency across the story set"
}
Do not include any markdown formatting, backticks, or extra text. Output only the raw JSON.
